cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper presents a new training method for support vector machines (SVMs), which are commonly used in machine learning for classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary category for papers on SVMs. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of dropout, a popular regularization technique in deep learning, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also includes experiments on real datasets, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
